      "value": "Vallecitos Elementary is a very small elementary (K-6) district in eastern San Diego County, serving about 32 students with an IEP. The number of autistic students is small enough that the state does not report it separately, so this profile describes all students with disabilities rather than autism specifically. About 78% of students with disabilities spend most of the school day in a general-education classroom."
    },
    "what_this_means_for_parents": {
      "ai_disclaimer": "This summary was written by an AI model from the data points in this profile. The underlying numbers come from public California government sources, but the narrative is AI-written and may contain inaccuracies. Verify specific claims directly with the school district before making decisions.",
      "ai_generated": true,
