      "ai_model": "claude-opus (via Claude Code session)",
      "based_on_sources": [
        "cde_spedps",
        "ca_dashboard"
      ],
      "value": "Autism-specific counts are not separately reported for a district this small, so the figures here describe all students with disabilities together. About 78% are in a general-education classroom for most of the school day. On 2024-25 state tests, students with disabilities scored about 63 points below standard in English and 112 below in math, compared with 1 and 54 points below for students overall. Students with disabilities were chronically absent at about 3% \u2014 lower than the 9% rate for all students \u2014 and were suspended at about 5%."
    }
